==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lauric
<hw>Lau"ric</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Pertaining
to, or derived from, the European bay or laurel (<spn>Laurus
nobilis</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>pertaining to or combined with <er>lauric acid</er>,
the 12-carbon member of the fatty acid series; combined with the acyl
group of lauric acid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lauric acid</ent>⟦br⟧
